🌍 II. REAL-WORLD VERSION (People Actually Get Paid)

Now let’s ground your core idea:

People get paid to run structured, useful experiments in reality

This is the part that can actually ship.

⸻

🧪 The Clean Model

“Quest = Paid Micro-Experiment”

Each quest is:
	•	a hypothesis
	•	tested via real-world action
	•	producing structured data

⸻

🔹 Examples (Real, Valuable)

🏪 Retail Behavior

“Rearrange 3 items in a store. Record change in interaction.”

⸻

🧠 Decision Psychology

“Ask 5 people why they chose X over Y. Capture reasoning.”

⸻

🌆 Urban Design

“Time how long it takes people to cross this area at different times.”

⸻

🗣️ Cultural Translation

“Explain this phrase to someone outside your culture. Record confusion points.”

⸻

🧪 Micro A/B Testing (Powerful)

“Try two ways of presenting the same idea. Which works better?”

⸻

💰 Payment Model (Realistic)

Each quest gets:
	•	Base pay ($1–$20 depending on complexity)
	•	Bonus for quality
	•	Bonus for rarity
	•	Bonus for validated accuracy

⸻

Example:
	•	simple observation → $2–5
	•	structured experiment → $10–30
	•	rare / high-skill → $50+

⸻

🧠 Who Pays?

This is key.

⸻

🏢 Buyers
	•	AI companies (training + grounding)
